Connect to server - 
mysql -h localhost -u root -p

MariaDB[none] - none means data base is not created

Creating a database -

CREATE DATABASE databasename;

CREATE DATABASE ss91db;

Check databases - 
SHOW DATABASES;

Select database - 
USE ss91db;

Datatypes
-> numeric(numbers)
1. int(tinyint, smallint, mediumint, int, bidint)
2. decimalvalues(float, double, decimal(maximum_digits, decimal_places))
decimal(5,2) - 999.99 is max value, 5 digit with 3 decimal places

-> Character 
1. char(max_len)
2. varchar(max_len)
name char(10) - Riya******  - It allocates 10 bytes always
name varchar(10)  - Riya*   - It allocates +1 byte only so required less memory
3. text

-> datetime
date yyyy-mm-dd
time hh:mm:ss
datetime yyyy-mm-dd hh:mm:ss

-> binary - It is used to store images, binary data
1. byte
2. binary
3. blob - to store character or file

constraints
1. Primary key
2. foreign key
3. unique
4. not null
5. default

Database object - whatever created inside the database using CREATE command.

